# AI Work Progress - Sweet.TV Kodi Addon

## Project Goal
Build a Kodi addon for sweet.tv that provides native TV experience (live channels, EPG, archive, VOD) using IPTV Manager integration.

## Phases

### Phase 1: Core Live TV + EPG [IN PROGRESS - tested on Linux Mint Flatpak Kodi]
- [x] Analyze Enigma2 reference plugin for API understanding
- [x] Plan architecture and discuss with user
- [x] Set up repo structure (README, configs, addon skeleton)
- [x] Implement sweet.tv API client (auth, channels, EPG, streams)
- [x] Implement IPTV Manager integration (channels + EPG via socket)
- [x] Build addon entry point and URL router
- [x] Create settings UI (bitrate, adult filter, pairing)
- [x] Implement device pairing flow with on-screen dialogs
- [x] Implement live stream playback (uses inputstream.adaptive directly with master HLS playlist)
- [x] Live TV channel browsing with categories
- [ ] Verify channels appear in Kodi's native TV section via IPTV Manager
- [ ] Fix category names (currently empty - API field names unknown, debug logging added)

### Phase 2: Archive/Catchup [WORKING via addon UI]
- [x] Browse channels with archive support
- [x] Browse archive by day
- [x] Play archived programs (works through addon UI)
- [ ] Catchup integration via PVR (catchup_source in IPTV Manager streams)

### Phase 3: Parental Lock [PLANNED]
