### Build & Distribution [DONE]
- [x] Makefile with build/release/clean/version targets
- [x] Date-based versioning (YYYY.MM.DD with .N suffix for intra-day rebuilds)
- [x] GitHub releases via `make release`
- [x] Repository addon (repository.sweettv) for auto-updates
- [x] addons.xml + addons.xml.md5 generation in `repo/`
- [ ] GitHub Pages hosting for repo (using raw GitHub URLs for now)

## Known Issues / Lessons Learned
- IPTV Manager and PVR Simple Client CANNOT be declared as Kodi dependencies — install fails. Users must install them manually from Kodi's repo.
- Kodi rejects ZIP install if same version is already installed — must bump version on each rebuild.
- Manual HLS variant parsing was unreliable — passing master playlist directly to inputstream.adaptive works for all channels.
- After failed installs, sometimes need to clear `~/.var/app/tv.kodi.Kodi/data/addons/plugin.video.sweettv` and `addon_data/plugin.video.sweettv`.

## Technical Decisions
- IPTV Manager for native TV section (user choice)
- Kodi 21+ only, no legacy support
- English first, localization later
- Device pairing auth (not username/password — API requirement)
- inputstream.adaptive handles HLS quality selection (not us)
- GNU sed (gsed) used in Makefile, not BSD sed

## Architecture

```
sweet.tv API
    ↕
sweettv_api.py (auth, channels, EPG, streams, movies, search)
    ↕
addon.py (URL router) + service.py (stream cleanup, IPTV Manager bridge)
    ↕
IPTV Manager (channels + EPG via socket)
    ↕
PVR IPTV Simple Client
    ↕
Kodi TV Section
```

## File Layout
```
plugin.video.sweettv/
  addon.xml          - manifest with IPTV Manager config
  addon.py           - URL router and all action handlers
  service.py         - background service for stream lifecycle
  resources/
    settings.xml     - addon settings
    language/.../strings.po
    lib/
      sweettv_api.py - API client
      iptv_manager.py - IPTV Manager socket integration

repository.sweettv/
  addon.xml          - Kodi repo pointer to raw GitHub

repo/
  addons.xml         - generated by `make repo-index`
  addons.xml.md5

Makefile             - build, release, version targets
```

## Reference
- Enigma2 plugin: tmp/archivczsk-doplnky/plugin_video_sweettv/ (gitignored)
- sweet.tv API: https://api.sweet.tv/ (all POST, JSON)
- IPTV Manager: https://github.com/add-ons/service.iptv.manager
- PVR Simple Client: https://github.com/kodi-pvr/pvr.iptvsimple
